


Q4) Write down the responsibilities of the Jdbc Client.

Ans:->

	JDBC makes it possible to do establish a connection with a data source, 
	send queries and update statements, and process the results.
	
	//Simply, JDBC makes it possible to do the following things within a Java application:
		1) Establish a connection with a data source.
		2) Send queries and update statements to the data source.
		3)Process the results.
		
		The Java application calls JDBC classes and interfaces to submit SQL statements and retrieve results.

	//The JDBC API is implemented through the JDBC driver. 
	//The JDBC Driver is a set of classes that implement the JDBC interfaces to process JDBC calls and 
	return result sets to a Java application. The database (or data store) stores the data retrieved by 
	the application using the JDBC Driver.
	